comments.text:
The "could not determine packageUrl property" message comes from mozharness since the build properties aren't set. However, the build properties aren't being set because the build is failing (it looks like all these cases are failing in 'make upload'?)

jlund: Should we be reporting this error in mozharness if the build is failing? When upload fails, mach should be returning an error code to mozharness, so maybe it shouldn't bother looking for build properties in that case. Mozharness could either say nothing, or give a more general "build failed - see above log for details" message.

General question: Why is stage.mozilla.org so dodgy? These are all connection timeouts to stage.m.o, either from an scp or ssh command.
comments.author: mshal@mozilla.com

comments.text: I'll try to work around this issue with bug 1118774, and I've filed bug 1118778 for the mozharness error reporting. Bug 1118782 can be a followup so that we know how often our connections actually fail, so we can determine if we need a more reliable upload mechanism.
